That caution comes in part from reactions to some of the formulas in which the quickly created 2009 pandemic flu vaccine was delivered.
(That version was not used in the 2009 US campaign and is not sold in the US now.)
Vaccines save lives and reduce illnesses and, if the Covid-19 pandemic proceeds as it has the past few months, any new vaccine against it could be in high demand.
Nations fortunate enough to house one have committed to the WHO to share their products equitably worldwide.
In the United States, administering public health is a state power.